'''Eddie Miles''' (born September 13, 1968) is a former [[American football]] [[linebacker]] who played one season with the [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] of the [[National Football League]]. He was drafted by the Pittsburgh Steelers in the tenth round of the [[1990 NFL Draft]]. He played [[college football]] at the [[University of Minnesota]] and attended [[Miami Springs High School]] in [[Miami Springs, Florida]].

